# Micro-commits (required)

After **every** completed logical change in this repo, create a **separate git commit** before continuing or ending the session. Do not accumulate multi-topic diffs across a conversation.

**Micro means small.** A good commit is usually **1–5 files**, **one concern**, and easy to review in under a minute. If a commit touches multiple sites, multiple layers (source + unrelated generated HTML), or both docs and product code, **split it**.

## Hard limits (default)

| Rule | Guideline |
|------|-----------|
| Files per commit | Prefer **1–3**, max **~8** only when source + its single generated output |
| Sites per commit | **One site folder** (`sites/<name>/`) unless the change is repo-root tooling that affects all sites equally |
| Topics per commit | **One**: e.g. tokens only, fonts only, FAQ copy only, one build output |
| Bad lump | ❌ “Brand powerbuilding site” with 38 files — split into tokens → fonts → copy sources → rebuild |

## When to commit

Commit immediately after each focused unit, for example:

- One feature or fix (even small)
- Build output regeneration **in the commit immediately after** the source commit (or same commit only if ≤2 files: e.g. `build.mjs` + one `index.html`)
- CSS-only vs JS-only vs data/build-only → **always separate** when independent
- Each **sister site** branded → separate commit per site, per layer when possible

## When the session ends

1. Run `git status`.
2. If anything is modified or staged, commit it in logical chunks **or** tell the user explicitly what remains uncommitted and why.
3. Never imply work is "done" while `programs.css`, `build.mjs`, generated HTML, etc. are still dirty.

## Commit style

- Follow the repo's existing message style (short subject, complete sentence, focus on **why**).
- Use HEREDOC for commit messages.
- Do **not** commit secrets, `.env`, or `*.code-workspace` unless the user asks.
- Do **not** push unless asked.
- Obey git safety rules (no `--no-verify`, no amend unless allowed, no force-push to main).

## Splitting guidance

| Change type | Commits (typical) |
|-------------|-------------------|
| FAQ data change | 1) `faq-data.js` 2) `npm run build:faq` → `faq/index.html` + landing FAQ patch |
| Theme tokens | 1) `design-tokens.css` only |
| Fonts | 1) `fonts.css` + font `<link>` in HTML |
| Landing copy | 1) `index.html` hero/meta only |
| Repo script | 1) `scripts/*.mjs` only — not bundled with site HTML |
| Three clone sites | **Three commits minimum** (one per site), not one |

If the user asks "micro committed?" or similar, check `git status` first; if dirty, commit now in logical slices. If past commits were too large, do not rewrite history unless asked — apply this rule going forward.

## Example flow

1. Edit `programs/build.mjs` → run build → commit build + `programs/index.html`.
2. Edit `programs.css` → commit styles.
3. Edit `programs.js` → commit behavior.

Three commits, not one lump at the end.
